<chapter id="IC2D_EclipsePlugin">
    
    <title>IC2D: Interactive Control and Debugging of Distribution and Eclipse plugin</title>
    
    
    <para>
        IC2D is a tool, which enables you to <emphasis role="bold">launch</emphasis>,
        <emphasis role="bold">monitor</emphasis> and <emphasis role="bold">control</emphasis>
        ProActive distributed and grid applications.
    </para>
    <para>
        IC2D is available in two forms :
    </para>
    <itemizedlist>
        <listitem><para>
            A <emphasis role="bold">Java standalone application</emphasis> available
            for all the platforms,
        </para></listitem>
        <listitem><para>
            An <emphasis role="bold">Eclipse plugin</emphasis>, this plugin also proposes
            functionalities for facilitating the development of applications using ProActive
            (TODO a short list ...).
        </para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
        
    <!-- ************************************************************************************ -->
    
    <sect1 id="MonitoringControl">
        
        <title>Monitoring and Control</title>
        
        <para>
            The <emphasis role="bold">Monitoring plugin</emphasis> provides a <emphasis role="bold">graphical visualisation</emphasis> for hosts,
            Java Virtual Machines, and active objects, including the topology and the volume of
            communications. And the <emphasis role="bold">Job Monitoring plugin</emphasis> provides a 
            <emphasis role="bold">tree representation</emphasis> of all these objects.
        </para>
        
        <para>
            In order to monitor a new host, open the <emphasis role="bold">Monitoring Perspective</emphasis>
            and select <emphasis role="bold">Monitoring->Monitor a new host...</emphasis> :
        </para>
        
        <figure id="monitorNewHost">
            <title>Dialog in which you specify the host to be monitored</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ic2d/images/features/monitor_new_host.png" format="PNG"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
        
        <para>
        	Then you can observe in the <emphasis role="bold">Monitoring view</emphasis> a graphical
        	representation of the activity of the host.
        </para>
        
        <para>
        	And if you want to observe the <emphasis role="bold">tree representation</emphasis>,
        	open the <emphasis role="bold">Job Monitoring view</emphasis>:
        </para>
        
        <figure id="openJobMonitoringView">
            <title>Select the Job Monitoring view in the list</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ic2d/images/features/showViewJobMonitoring.png" format="PNG"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
        
   		<para>
   			The <xref linkend="monitoring"/> is an example of what you can obtain.
   		</para>
        
        <figure id="monitoring">
            <title>Monitoring of 2 applications</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="ic2d/images/features/RunMonitoring3.png" format="PNG"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
        
    </sect1> <!-- Monitoring and Control -->
    
    <!-- ************************************************************************************ -->
    
    <sect1 id="LauncherScheduler">
        
        <title>Launcher and Scheduler</title>
        
        <sect2>
            <title>Launcher in IC2D</title>
            
            <para>
                In order to open a deployment descriptor select : Launcher > <emphasis role="bold">Open an XML file
                </emphasis>. Next select your deployment file. Then, the <emphasis role="bold">Launcher pespective</emphasis> will open.
            </para>
            
            <para>
                <figure>
                    <title>The launcher menu</title>
                    
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="ic2d/images/features/launcher_menu.png" format="PNG"  contentwidth="100" width="6in"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </figure>
            </para>
            
            <para>
                Now, the Launcher perspective is open.
            </para>
            
            <para>
                <figure>
                    <title>The Launcher perspective</title>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="ic2d/images/features/Launcher.png" format="PNG"  contentwidth="100" width="6in"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </figure>
            </para>
            
            <para>
                This perspective contains an <emphasis role="bold">XML editor</emphasis>, a <emphasis role="bold">console</emphasis>,
                and the <emphasis role="bold">list of opened deployment descriptors</emphasis>.
            </para>
            
            <para>
                To <emphasis role="bold">launch</emphasis> an application, you have several possibilities :
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Click on the button of the main menu bar, the file which is in the active editor will be launched.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Select your file in the xml descriptors list, and click on the launch icon in the popup menu.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Select your file in the xml descriptors list, and click on the launch icon on the menu bar of the application list.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </para>
            
            <para>
                You can kill the applications launched from a popup-menu in the "Deployment descriptors" list.
            </para>
            
            <para>
                To see your application running, open the "Monitoring perspective" and monitor the corresponding host.
            </para>
        </sect2>
        
        
    </sect1><!-- Launcher and Scheduler -->
    
